eachings of Presidents of the Church: Joseph Smith</a></em> (2007), 28.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note6-"><span class="label">6. </span><p data-aid="138543610" id="note6_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/pgp/js-h/1.html?verse=8#p8" href="/scriptures/pgp/js-h/1.8?lang=eng#p8">Joseph Smith—History 1:8</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note7-"><span class="label">7. </span><p data-aid="138543613" id="note7_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/pgp/js-h/1.html?verse=10#p10" href="/scriptures/pgp/js-h/1.10?lang=eng#p10">Joseph Smith—History 1:10</a>; emphasis added.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note8-"><span class="label">8. </span><p data-aid="138543616" id="note8_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/acts/10.html?verse=38#p38" href="/scriptures/nt/acts/10.38?lang=eng#p38">Acts 10:38</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note9-"><span class="label">9. </span><p data-aid="138543619" id="note9_p1">Bonnie D. Parkin, “<a href="http://speeches.byu.edu/talks/bonnie-d-parkin_personal-ministry-sacred-precious">Personal Ministry: Sacred and Precious</a>” (Brigham Young University devotional, Feb. 13, 2007), 1, speeches.byu.edu.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note10-"><span class="label">10. </span><p data-aid="138543621" id="note10_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/bofm/moro/7.html?verse=13#p13" href="/scriptures/bofm/moro/7.13?lang=eng#p13">Moroni 7:13</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note11-"><span class="label">11. </span><p data-aid="138543624" id="note11_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/1-cor/13.html?verse=8#p8" href="/scriptures/nt/1-cor/13.8?lang=eng#p8">1 Corinthians 13:8</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note12-"><span class="label">12. </span><p data-aid="138543626" id="note12_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/bofm/2-ne/32.html?verse=5#p5" href="/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/32.5?lang=eng#p5">2 Nephi 32:5</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note13-"><span class="label">13. </span><p data-aid="138543627" id="note13_p1">“I can do all things through Christ which strengtheneth me” (<a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/philip/4.html?verse=13#p13" href="/scriptures/nt/philip/4.13?lang=eng#p13">Philippians 4:13</a>).</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note14-"><span class="label">14. </span><p data-aid="138543629" id="note14_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/heb/4.html?verse=16#p16" href="/scriptures/nt/heb/4.16?lang=eng#p16">Hebrews 4:16</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note15-"><span class="label">15. </span><p data-aid="138544631" id="note15_p1">“And if men come unto me I will show unto them their weakness. I give unto men weakness that they may be humble; and my <em>grace</em> is sufficient for all men that humble themselves before me; for if they humble themselves before me, and have faith in me, then will I make weak things become strong unto them” (<a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/bofm/ether/12.html?verse=27#p27" href="/scriptures/bofm/ether/12.27?lang=eng#p27">Ether 12:27</a>; emphasis added).</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note16-"><span class="label">16. </span><p data-aid="138544632" id="note16_p1">See <a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/matt/14.html?verse=13-21#p13" href="/scriptures/nt/matt/14.13-21?lang=eng#p13">Matthew 14:13–21</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/mark/6.html?verse=31-44#p31" href="/scriptures/nt/mark/6.31-44?lang=eng#p31">Mark 6:31–44</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/luke/9.html?verse=10-17#p10" href="/scriptures/nt/luke/9.10-17?lang=eng#p10">Luke 9:10–17</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/john/6.html?verse=1-14#p1" href="/scriptures/nt/john/6.1-14?lang=eng#p1">John 6:1–14</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note17-"><span class="label">17. </span><p data-aid="138544633" id="note17_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/john/6.html?verse=9#p9" href="/scriptures/nt/john/6.9?lang=eng#p9">John 6:9</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note18-"><span class="label">18. </span><p data-aid="138544634" id="note18_p1">President Boyd K. Packer taught: “However many generations in your mortal ancestry, no matter what race or people you represent, the pedigree of your spirit can be written on a single line. You are a child of God!” (“<a class="cross-ref" data-old-href="../../../../general-conference/1989/04/to-young-women-and-men.html" href="/general-conference/1989/04/to-young-women-and-men">To Young Women and Men</a>,” <em>Ensign,</em> May 1989, 54).</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note19-"><span class="label">19. </span><p data-aid="138544635" id="note19_p1">C. S. Lewis, <em>Mere Christianity</em> (1960), 160.</p></li></ol></footer>
